The article discusses the need for legislative reforms to protect the American people in light of the recent attempted mass murder attack in New York City. The author emphasizes the importance of fixing the immigration system to prevent dangerous individuals from entering the country. They also call for an end to chain migration and propose other measures to enhance domestic security, such as increasing the number of Immigration and Customs Enforcement officers and addressing fraud and abuse in the immigration system. Additionally, the author argues that those convicted of acts of terror should face the strongest penalty allowed by law, including the death penalty in appropriate cases.